Description: "Wine Dark Open Sea"---Paul McCartney Was the man singing about this magnificent Nitrocellulose Lacquer finished Wine Red stunner? Perhaps. This mint or very near mint 2016 Gibson ES-339 Studio sizzles with pure tone. It can effortlessly switch between smooth as butter or down and dirty grit. From the creators of this MADE IN AMERICA masterwork ax: "Close to the size of a Les Paul, this affordable model features the same great-sounding '57 Classic (neck) and Super '57 Classic (bridge) pickups and semi-hollowbody design of its siblings minus the binding and block inlays. It comes with simplified controls, soft C profile playing, redesigned neck dimensions, an improved truss rod system, rolled neck binding, low profile frets, Grover tuners and locking stopbar tailpiece. Includes hardshell case." The ES-339 Studio delivers impressive value with '57 Classic and Super '57 Classic humbucking pickups, traditional control setup and rolled fingerboard edges for a delightful playing feel.
